:: Surface Admin First Visit [surface]
[img[setup.ImagePath+'Surface/administration.png']]

As you approach the heart of Outset Town, a sturdy building looms before you. While not particularly grandiose, its facade of polished stone and modest columns lends it an air of authority. A wooden sign proclaims this structure as the town's Administrative Center.

The building's entrance bustles with activity. Divers, merchants, and locals alike stream in and out, seemingly too focused on their own business to notice you. The only hint that this building is near the Abyss are an occasional person with a minor inhuman characteristic, such as a young woman with elf ears, a young boy with a cat tail swaying behind him, or a man who seems more seasoned with scaly skin. Through the open doors, you catch glimpses of various service counters, each dedicated to the unique needs of a town living in the shadow of the unknown.

To your right, a animated conversation catches your attention. A man with tanned skin and striking green eyes leans casually against a pillar, his brown hair tousled as if by a playful breeze. His charismatic presence seems to light up the space around him as he chats with a female loan officer. Their hushed tones and the man's persuasive gestures suggest a discussion about someone's debt, though his charm appears to be working its magic on the stern-faced official.

