:: Surface Relic First Visit [surface]

As you approach the Relic shop, your eyes are immediately drawn to the eclectic display in the window. Objects both mundane and extraordinary jostle for space, each one a potential treasure from the depths of the Abyss. A sign above the door proclaims "Relics Bought and Sold" in bright red letters.

Pushing open the door, you're greeted by a cacophony of sights and sounds. Shelves line the walls, crammed with an assortment of items that defy easy categorization. A pillow, looking just a touch too fluffy to be ordinary, sits next to a set of seemingly normal cooking pans. Your gaze is drawn to a small rock covered in pulsing red runes, and then to a fish-shaped water bottle that appears to wiggle every few moments.

Behind the counter, a middle-aged man with a skinny build and a gray ivy cap busies himself with various gadgets and gizmos. His sharp eyes dart between the items and a peculiar handheld meter, suggesting a method to his apparent madness of valuation.

As you take in the surroundings, your attention is caught by a figure weaving through the cluttered aisles. At first glance, you see a young woman in a cute dress, but as they turn, you realize it's actually a very feminine young man. His androgynous features are framed by striking blue hair that matches his wide, wonder-filled eyes. He moves from shelf to shelf with an air of fascination, fingers hovering just shy of touching the mysterious Relics.

