As you approach the item store, you're greeted by a large, practical-looking building with wide display windows. Unlike the mysterious allure of the Relic shop, this establishment exudes a sense of pragmatism and necessity. A wilderness-themed sign above the entrance reads "Outset Outfitters: Everything a Diver Needs".

Stepping inside, you're immediately struck by the sheer variety of goods on offer. Shelves and racks stretch from floor to ceiling, laden with all manner of supplies essential for those brave (or foolish) enough to venture into the Abyss. The air is thick with the mingled scents of leather, metal, and preserved foods.

Your eyes roam over long-lasting rations stacked neatly beside rows of disposable water bottles and sturdy refillable flasks. One wall is dedicated to an impressive array of weapons - gleaming swords hang next to locked cases containing handguns of various calibers. Nearby, you spot neatly organized medkits, high-powered flashlights, coils of durable rope, and compasses guaranteed to function even in the Abyss's strange environment.

However, it's a section near the back that truly captures your attention. Here, unique items unavailable anywhere else are displayed prominently. A leather-bound tome with "Encyclopedia Abyssia" embossed in gold lettering sits on a pedestal, promising knowledge of the mysterious depths. Beside it, a curious collection of balloons with integrated pulley systems catches your eye. And finally, you notice a small shelf where two arm braces made of faintly glowing white wood rest, their otherworldly appearance hinting at powerful protective properties.

But suddenly, a commotion near the counter draws your attention. A young woman with vibrant lavender hair is engaged in an animated discussion with the shopkeeper. Her energy is palpable as she gesticulates wildly, pointing to a colorful book - unmistakably a manga - and then to a nearby shelf of practical items. The shopkeeper's bemused expression suggests this isn't an uncommon occurrence.

