:: Surface Exit First Visit [surface]

As you approach the outskirts of Outset Town, the bustling sounds of commerce and chatter gradually fade, replaced by an eerie stillness. The path beneath your feet becomes rougher, transitioning from well-worn cobblestones to jagged rock. Ahead, you see the terrain suddenly drop away, marking the precipice of the infamous Abyss.

Drawing closer, you're struck by the sheer scale of what lies before you. The Abyss yawns open, a colossal maw in the earth that seems to defy comprehension. Its edges are ragged and uneven, as if the ground itself was violently torn asunder by some unimaginable force. Wisps of an otherworldly mist curl upwards from the depths, obscuring your view of what lies below.

A strange wind rises to meet you, carrying with it scents and sensations entirely foreign to the surface world. It's not a gust from any cardinal direction, but rather an upward draft from the very bowels of the earth.

Near the edge, atop a jutting rock formation, sits a solitary figure. A young woman with hair as vivid as fresh blood, contrasting sharply with her dull gray-green sweatshirt. Her posture is hunched, her gaze fixed unwaveringly on the Abyss before her. There's a stillness about her that goes beyond mere physical immobility – as if her very spirit has been caught in the Abyss's gravitational pull.

